summary:
At the very outset, let me introduce myself, I am Fouzia Sharif, 25 years old, born in Pakistan and currently living in the Netherlands for the last one and half years.

As far as my educational qualification is concerned, I did my Masters in Computer Sciences from Government College Women University, Faisalabad (GCWUF) Pakistan. 

I have an expertise in different programming languages i.e. HTML, Javascript, CSS, PHP, WordPress, MySQL, React JS. It is pertinent to mention here that I have close insight over object oriented programming (OPP) and Data Structure. 

Currently I am working remotely  with a Pakistani Company " Beaconsofts" as a frontend developer.
As a frontend developer my responsibilities is to:
Determining the structure and design of web pages.
Ensuring user experience determines design choices.
Developing features to enhance the user experience.
Striking a balance between functional and aesthetic design.
Ensuring web design is optimized for smartphones.
Building reusable code for future use.
Optimizing web pages for maximum speed and scalability.
Utilizing a variety of markup languages to write web pages.
Maintaining brand consistency throughout the design, and I ensure the company's website is functioning properly for users and customers. Employees will report to me if they see any troubles with the website and I will use my coding skills to resolve these issues. I regularly scan the website for any user issues and will provide regular updates and enhancements. I also apply collaborative skills when meeting with the creative team to ensure their front-end design aligns well with  back-end design.
